00:18:01,910 --> 00:18:08,60
- YEAH.

219
00:18:08,80 --> 00:18:13,000
- HERE'S THE GRASS THAT
ALEUTS FED TO THE RUSSIANS
WHEN THEY FIRST GOT HERE.

220
00:18:13,20 --> 00:18:17,40
LOT OF THEM HAD SCURVY
OR SOME SORT OF SICKNESS.

221
00:18:17,60 --> 00:18:21,470
THERE WAS NO DOCTORS HERE,
EITHER, YOU KNOW, FOR YEARS.

222
00:18:21,490 --> 00:18:23,10
DIDN'T HAVE A CLINIC HERE.

223
00:18:23,30 --> 00:18:27,810
- YEAH.

224
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:31,449
- GONNA CUT ONE OFF.

225
00:18:31,470 --> 00:18:37,690
AND WHAT THEY DO IS CHOP IT UP
AND BOIL IT,

226
00:18:37,710 --> 00:18:40,990
AND WHAT COMES OUT OF THE LEAVES
AND OUT OF THE VINES,

227
00:18:41,10 --> 00:18:42,30
THEY DRINK IT.

228
00:18:42,50 --> 00:18:45,330
IT'S LIKE A TEA.

229
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:49,570
TRY ONE OF THESE HERE.
THEY'RE--ONCE YOU CHEW ON THEM--

230
00:18:49,590 --> 00:18:52,510
YOU'LL FIND IT VERY BITTER.

231
00:18:52,530 --> 00:18:56,139
- IT'S KIND OF LIKE
IF YOU LEFT SOME SOAP

232
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:58,210
AND YOU TASTED IT,
THAT'S THE BITTER.

233
00:18:58,230 --> 00:19:01,850
- YEAH.

234
00:19:01,870 --> 00:19:06,449
SAVED A LOT OF RUSSIANS' LIVES,
AND MAYBE THEY SHOULDN'T HAVE.

235
00:19:06,470 --> 00:19:08,820
OR THERE'D PROBABLY BE
MORE OF US AROUND TODAY.

236
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:11,419
[LAUGHTER]

237
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:26,940
- [MAN SINGING
IN UNANGAM TUNUU]

238
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:30,710
- ONE OF THOSE RUSSIANS SAVED
WAS MY GREAT-GREAT-GRANDFATHER

239
00:19:30,730 --> 00:19:33,950
MIKHAIL LESTENKOF.

240
00:19:33,970 --> 00:19:40,390
HE BEGINS THE RUSSIAN CHAPTER
OF MY FAMILY HISTORY.

241
00:19:40,410 --> 00:19:44,90
MIKHAIL WAS BORN
DURING THE REIGN OF
CATHERINE THE GREAT,

242
00:19:44,110 --> 00:19:46,389
AT A TIME WHEN
THE RUSSIAN EMPIRE

243
00:19:46,410 --> 00:19:51,100
WAS GROWING RICHER
THROUGH THE FUR TRADE.

244
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:54,30
MIKHAIL WAS ONE OF HUNDREDS
OF YOUNG RUSSIAN MEN

245
00:19:54,50 --> 00:19:56,600
CALLED PROMYSHLENNIKI.

246
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:58,239
THEY WERE TRAPPERS AND TRADERS

247
00:19:58,260 --> 00:20:01,840
WHO WERE THE BACKBONE
OF THIS SOFT GOLD RUSH.

248
00:20:01,860 --> 00:20:06,350
- THE FIRST RUSSIANS WHO CAME
TO ALASKA AND THE ALEUTIAN CHAIN

249
00:20:06,370 --> 00:20:09,449
WERE MARINE MAMMAL HUNTERS,

250
00:20:09,470 --> 00:20:13,320
AND MOSTLY WHAT ATTRACTED THEM
WAS THE SEA OTTER,

251
00:20:13,340 --> 00:20:17,720
BECAUSE SEA OTTERS BROUGHT
EXCEEDINGLY HIGH PRICES.

252
00:20:17,740 --> 00:20:24,260
SO THAT WAS WORTH THE RISKS.

253
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:29,399
- MIKHAIL TRAVELED OVER LAND
THOUSANDS OF MILES...

254
00:20:29,420 --> 00:20:32,70
THEN HE SET SAIL
FOR BERING ISLAND,

255
00:20:32,90 --> 00:20:38,10
WHERE HE FIRST ENCOUNTERED
THE UNANGAN.

256
00:20:38,30 --> 00:20:42,520
- WHAT THE RUSSIANS FOUND
WERE 30,000 HIGHLY ORGANIZED,

257
00:20:42,540 --> 00:20:45,590
SUPERBLY ADAPTED MARINE HUNTERS,

258
00:20:45,610 --> 00:20:48,389
AND THEY WERE ABLE TO TAKE
ADVANTAGE OF THOSE

259
00:20:48,410 --> 00:20:51,320
TECHNOLOGICAL SKILLS
AND THAT KNOW-HOW

260
00:20:51,340 --> 00:20:57,659
TO FORM THE FOUNDATION
OF THEIR FUR TRADE EMPIRE.

261
00:20:57,680 --> 00:21:01,470
- IN 1805, A RUSSIAN SHIP--
"CONSTANTINE"--

262
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:07,440
DROPPED MIKHAIL AND 11 OTHERS
ON BERING ISLAND.

263
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:11,580
FOR 7 YEARS, THEY HAD NO CONTACT
WITH THE OUTSIDE WORLD,

264
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:18,20
AND THEY SURVIVED ONLY BECAUSE
OF UNANGAN GENEROSITY.

265
00:21:18,40 --> 00:21:22,260
MIKHAIL BECAME A MANAGER IN
THE RUSSIAN-AMERICAN COMPANY,

266
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:25,90
WHICH WAS THE MONOPOLY
THAT RAN THE FUR EMPIRE

267
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:27,260
IN THE ALEUTIANS,

268
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:34,230
AND HE ENDED UP
MARRYING NEDEZHDA.

269
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:35,900
- WHEN PEOPLE IN THE ALEUTIANS

270
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:39,40
CAME IN CONTACT WITH
THE RUSSIANS FOR THE FIRST TIME,

271
00:21:39,60 --> 00:21:44,810
THEY WERE IRREVOCABLY
LINKED INTO THE WORLD ECONOMY.

272
00:21:44,830 --> 00:21:47,879
MARKET FORCES
IN OTHER CONTINENTS

273
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:49,850
WOULD DIRECTLY
AFFECT THEIR LIVES

274
00:21:49,870 --> 00:21:52,290
THROUGH THE RUSSIAN FUR TRADE
IN TERMS OF

275
00:21:52,310 --> 00:21:55,389
THE AVAILABILITY AND TYPES
OF TRADE GOODS

276
00:21:55,410 --> 00:22:03,200
THAT WERE ENTERING
THEIR MATERIAL CULTURE.

277
00:22:03,220 --> 00:22:07,130
- SOME RUSSIANS, LIKE MY
GREAT-GREAT-GRANDFATHER MIKHAIL,

278
00:22:07,150 --> 00:22:08,900
EMBRACED OUR PEOPLE'S WAYS,

279
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:16,580
BUT OTHERS, THEY JUST
SOUGHT ONLY TO CONQUER.

280
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:19,550
THE RUSSIANS, THEY BROUGHT
DISEASES THAT OUR PEOPLE

281
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:21,710
HAD NO IMMUNITY TO,

282
00:22:21,730 --> 00:22:25,550
AND WHEN THE UNANGAN REVOLTED
AGAINST RUSSIAN RULE,

283
00:22:25,570 --> 00:22:31,860
THEY WERE KILLED BY RUSSIAN
RIFLES AND SWORDS.

284
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,960
- AT THE POINT
OF RUSSIAN CONTACT,

285
00:22:33,980 --> 00:22:38,630
WITH THE INUIT PEOPLE
IN THE MID-18th CENTURY,

286
00:22:38,650 --> 00:22:41,870
THE ALEUTIAN ISLANDS WERE
FAR MORE DENSELY POPULATED

287
00:22:41,890 --> 00:22:44,900
THAN THEY ARE TODAY.

288
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:47,210
WITHIN THE FIRST 80 YEARS OR SO

289
00:22:47,230 --> 00:22:49,980
OF RUSSIAN OCCUPATION
OF THE ALEUTIANS,

290
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:57,920
THERE'S AN 80%
POPULATION DECLINE.

291
00:22:57,940 --> 00:23:01,690
WE REMEMBER THE BLACK DEATH
IN THE 1340s

292
00:23:01,710 --> 00:23:04,790
AS THIS DRAMATIC EVENT

293
00:23:04,810 --> 00:23:10,899
WHICH REALLY SHAPED THE COURSE
OF WESTERN CIVILIZATION.

294
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:14,230
BUT WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT THERE?

295
00:23:14,250 --> 00:23:20,870
I MEAN, YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT
30%, 1/3, 1/4.

296
00:23:20,890 --> 00:23:24,840
THIS IS 80%.

297
00:23:24,860 --> 00:23:40,389
IT'S AN ARMAGEDDON.

298
00:23:40,410 --> 00:23:43,530
- THIS SLAUGHTER OF
SO MANY OF MY PEOPLE

299
00:23:43,550 --> 00:23:49,970
LEFT A VOID THAT STILL
HANGS OVER THESE ISLANDS.

300
00:23:49,990 --> 00:23:53,140
THE SURVIVORS, THEY KEPT ALIVE
SOME TRADITIONAL WAYS,

301
00:23:53,160 --> 00:24:04,880
BUT MORE AND MORE, THE RUSSIAN
CULTURE TOOK HOLD.

302
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:07,450
MY GREAT-GRANDFATHER INNOKENTY

303
00:24:07,470 --> 00:24:12,790
WAS A FORCE
IN THAT TRANSFORMATION.

304
00:24:12,810 --> 00:24:18,000
HE WAS BORN ON THE ISLAND OF
ATTU IN 1832,

305
00:24:18,20 --> 00:24:21,430
AND AT SOME POINT, MID-LIFE,

306
00:24:21,450 --> 00:24:23,470
HE MOVED TO THE ISLAND
OF UNALASKA

307
00:24:23,490 --> 00:24:32,680
TO SERVE THE COMMUNITY THERE
AS A RUSSIAN ORTHODOX PRIEST.

308
00:24:32,700 --> 00:24:42,490
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

309
00:24:42,510 --> 00:24:47,790
- IT'S AMAZING TO ME HOW THROUGH
THE RUSSIAN ORTHODOX CHURCHES,

310
00:24:47,810 --> 00:24:49,899
WE STILL HAVE
THE PRESENCE OF RUSSIA.

311
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:51,430
AFTER ALL OF THESE YEARS.

312
00:24:51,450 --> 00:24:54,370
- ABSOLUTELY.
- WE STILL HAVE IT.

313
00:24:54,390 --> 00:24:57,840
SHARON SVARNY-LIVINGSTON
IS LIKE ME--

314
00:24:57,860 --> 00:25:02,639
TRYING TO BALANCE THE RUSSIAN
ORTHODOX FAITH WE WERE RAISED IN

315
00:25:02,660 --> 00:25:04,810
WITH THE TRADITIONAL
UNANGAN VALUES

316
00:25:04,830 --> 00:25:08,350
THAT WE BOTH WANT TO PRESERVE.

317
00:25:08,370 --> 00:25:10,679
- WHEN THE RUSSIANS FIRST CAME,

318
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:12,550
MODERN ARCHAEOLOGISTS SAY
THE POPULATION

319
00:25:12,570 --> 00:25:16,20
WAS SOMEWHERE BETWEEN
20,000 AND 25,000.

320
00:25:16,40 --> 00:25:19,590
THE FACT IS THAT WITHIN 40 YEARS
OF THE RUSSIANS COMING,

321
00:25:19,610 --> 00:25:22,899
THE POPULATION WAS
CUT DOWN TO ABOUT 3,000,

322
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:24,530
PROBABLY EVEN LOWER.

323
00:25:24,550 --> 00:25:26,899
UM, AND WHEN YOU THINK
ABOUT THOSE NUMBERS,

324
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:29,240
UNALASKA ISLAND ITSELF
HAD 3,000 PEOPLE ON IT

325
00:25:29,260 --> 00:25:31,000
BEFORE RUSSIAN CONTACT.

326
00:25:31,20 --> 00:25:36,879
WHO WENT FIRST?
THE CHIEFS, THE SHAMAN.

327
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:42,650
SO YOU LOST YOUR BASIS
FOR YOUR RELIGION.

328
00:25:42,670 --> 00:25:45,80
MISSIONARIES WITH INTENT

329
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:48,449
COME TO A PLACE AND INCORPORATE
TRADITIONS AND CULTURES

330
00:25:48,470 --> 00:25:51,90
INTO WHAT THEY'RE
TRYING TO BRING,

331
00:25:51,110 --> 00:25:54,760
AND, YOU KNOW, RUSSIAN ORTHODOXY
IS EXTREMELY RITUALISTIC.

332
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:56,860
SHAMANISM WAS VERY RITUALISTIC.

333
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:58,860
YOU KNOW, THEY BELIEVED
IN A GREATER BEING,

334
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:02,330
BUT IT WAS MORE TIED
TO THE ENVIRONMENT.

335
00:26:02,350 --> 00:26:05,770
AND I THINK THEY BROUGHT
THOSE THINGS INSIDE THE CHURCH

336
00:26:05,790 --> 00:26:08,909
TO MAKE IT AN EASIER TRANSITION
FOR THE PEOPLE.

337
00:26:08,930 --> 00:26:11,610
INSTEAD OF DOING IT OUTSIDE,
LET'S GO INSIDE AND DO IT.

338
00:26:11,630 --> 00:26:16,780
OK. YOU'RE GONNA BUILD
A INDOOR SPACE FOR US? SURE.

339
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:26,129
- [SINGING IN CHURCH SLAVONIC]

340
00:26:26,150 --> 00:26:30,130
- WHEN I LISTEN TO
THE YOUNG MEN SING HERE,

341
00:26:30,150 --> 00:26:36,70
I ALWAYS THINK ABOUT THE RUSSIAN
FUR HUNTER SHIPS' CREWS

342
00:26:36,90 --> 00:26:42,709
SINGING THE EVENING PRAYERS.

343
00:26:42,730 --> 00:26:46,610
EVERY SHIP CARRIED ICONS,
AND ON EVERY SHIP,

344
00:26:46,630 --> 00:26:52,590
THE CREW HELD SERVICES.

345
00:26:52,610 --> 00:26:58,189
I BELIEVE IN THE POWER OF MUSIC.

346
00:26:58,210 --> 00:27:02,760
ALEUTS ARE VERY MUSICAL PEOPLE,
AND I FIRMLY BELIEVE IN MY HEART

347
00:27:02,780 --> 00:27:11,40
THAT IT WAS THE MUSIC OF
THE SERVICE THAT ATTRACTED THEM.

348
00:27:11,60 --> 00:27:21,450
- [MAN RECITING
CHURCH SERVICE]

349
00:27:21,470 --> 00:27:26,950
- I ALWAYS HAVE TO WONDER
IF PEOPLE WERE REBELLIOUS

350
00:27:26,970 --> 00:27:30,920
WHEN RUSSIAN ORTHODOXY CAME.

351
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:33,660
I'M SURE THAT PROBABLY
SOME OF OUR PEOPLE SAID,

352
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:40,970
"WHAT ARE THEY DOING
WAVING THAT INCENSE AROUND?"

353
00:27:40,990 --> 00:27:43,140
- I WAS MYSTIFIED
WHEN I FIRST CAME TO ALASKA

354
00:27:43,160 --> 00:27:45,340
OVER 35 YEARS AGO--

355
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:48,409
WHY DO THE PEOPLE
IN THE ALEUTIAN CHAIN

356
00:27:48,430 --> 00:27:52,210
SO FERVENTLY HOLD ON
TO THIS ALIEN FAITH

357
00:27:52,230 --> 00:27:54,850
THAT HAD BEEN INTRODUCED TO THEM
FROM SIBERIA,

358
00:27:54,870 --> 00:27:56,580
NAMELY, THE RUSSIAN
ORTHODOX CHURCH?

359
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:59,80
IF THIS IS THE RELIGION OF THEIR
ENEMIES AND THEIR OPPRESSORS,

360
00:27:59,100 --> 00:28:00,419
WHY WASN'T IT ALL ABANDONED

361
00:28:00,440 --> 00:28:05,290
AS SOON AS THE RUSSIANS
WERE GONE?

362
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:08,590
IT SEEMS THAT THERE WAS
A WAY IN WHICH

363
00:28:08,610 --> 00:28:11,300
EASTERN CHRISTIANITY
RESONATED WITH

364
00:28:11,320 --> 00:28:15,100
THE ANCIENT TRIBAL BELIEFS
OF THE UNANGAN
AND THE ALUTIIQ PEOPLES.

365
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:18,40
THE MISSIONARIES TOOK THE TIME
TO LISTEN TO THE STORIES,

366
00:28:18,60 --> 00:28:21,240
ANALYZE THOSE STORIES,
AND BUILD ON THAT FOUNDATION.

367
00:28:21,260 --> 00:28:23,940
THEY CAME TO UNDERSTAND IT
IN THEIR OWN LANGUAGE

368
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:25,810
AND ADAPT IT TO THEIR OWN LIVES

369
00:28:25,830 --> 00:28:28,550
AS IT BECAME THE VERY CENTER OF
ALEUT CULTURAL IDENTITY

370
00:28:28,570 --> 00:28:30,679
AND ALEUT LIFE.

371
00:28:30,700 --> 00:28:33,850
- YOU ARE GIVEN BETTER TREATMENT
UNDER THE RUSSIAN RULES

372
00:28:33,870 --> 00:28:35,590
BY JOINING THE ORTHODOX CHURCH.

373
00:28:35,610 --> 00:28:38,459
IF YOU DID THAT, YOU WOULD BE
TREATED MUCH MORE CIVILLY,

374
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:39,660
SO A LOT OF PEOPLE DID.

375
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:42,30
AND WHEN THEY DID, THEY HAD TO
TAKE ON RUSSIAN NAMES

376
00:28:42,50 --> 00:28:44,629
WHEN YOU'RE BAPTIZED
IN RUSSIAN ORTHODOX CHURCH.

377
00:28:44,650 --> 00:28:47,230
THIS IS WHY MOST ALEUTS
HAVE RUSSIAN NAMES TODAY.

378
00:28:47,250 --> 00:28:57,140
[CHURCH BELLS RINGING]

379
00:28:57,160 --> 00:29:01,550
- ONCE WE GRAB ON TO SOMETHING,
WE DON'T WANT TO LET IT GO.

380
00:29:01,570 --> 00:29:02,720
WE MAKE IT OURS.

381
00:29:02,740 --> 00:29:05,80
- [MAN RECITING CHURCH SERVICE,
CHORAL RESPONSE]

382
00:29:05,100 --> 00:29:10,120
- BUT I ALSO THINK THE CHURCH
PROTECTED THE PEOPLE.

383
00:29:10,140 --> 00:29:14,160
NOT ONLY FROM THE RUSSIANS,
WHEN THEY WERE SO BRUTAL,

384
00:29:14,180 --> 00:29:18,760
BUT THEY PROTECTED PEOPLE
DURING THE AMERICANIZATION.

385
00:29:18,780 --> 00:29:21,70
LIKE DAD SAID,
YOU HAVE TO TAKE CARE

386
00:29:21,90 --> 00:29:22,399
OF SOMETHING THAT
TOOK CARE OF YOU.

387
00:29:22,420 --> 00:29:25,870
- THAT'S RIGHT.
- AND IT DID
TAKE CARE OF OUR PEOPLE

388
00:29:25,890 --> 00:29:30,80
THROUGH TRIALS AND TRIBULATIONS,
THROUGH DIFFERENT POLITICAL ERAS

389
00:29:30,100 --> 00:29:33,209
AND SOCIAL PRESSURES,
LANGUAGE CHANGES.

390
00:29:33,230 --> 00:29:44,760
- [PEOPLE SINGING HYMNS]

391
00:29:44,780 --> 00:29:47,60
- [MAN RECITING CHURCH SERVICE]

392
00:29:47,80 --> 00:29:51,560
- BUT HE ALSO SAID,
"SOMETIMES I LONG FOR THE DAYS

393
00:29:51,580 --> 00:29:55,530
WHEN MY PEOPLE RESPECTED
THE EARTH, SEA, AND SKY."

394
00:29:55,550 --> 00:29:58,500
AND I COULD SEE
THAT HE WAS TRYING

395
00:29:58,520 --> 00:30:01,770
TO HAVE THE BEST OF BOTH WORLDS.

396
00:30:01,790 --> 00:30:13,420
- AMEN.

397
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:17,60
- RUSSIAN ORTHODOX PRIESTS
CAN MARRY.

398
00:30:17,80 --> 00:30:21,530
MY GREAT-GRANDFATHER INNOKENTY
WAS MARRIED AND HAD CHILDREN,

399
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:28,770
AND HIS OLDEST SON DMITRI
WAS MY GRANDFATHER.

400
00:30:28,790 --> 00:30:33,10
MY GRANDFATHER DMITRI LESTENKOF
WORKED HERE ON UNALASKA

401
00:30:33,30 --> 00:30:38,139
IN THE EARLY 1880s FOR
THE ALASKA COMMERCIAL COMPANY.

402
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:41,380
AND THE ONLY THING THAT I CAN
FIND LEFT OF THAT COMPANY

403
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:51,890
IS THE A.C. VALUE CENTER, AS IN
ALASKA COMMERCIAL VALUE CENTER.

404
00:30:51,910 --> 00:30:54,830
BOTH MY GREAT-GRANDFATHER
INNOKENTY

405
00:30:54,850 --> 00:30:59,500
AND MY GRANDFATHER DMITRI HAD
UNANGAN BLOOD AND RUSSIAN BLOOD,

406
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:01,70
WHICH MADE THEM CREOLES.

407
00:31:01,90 --> 00:31:04,570
- [SINGING IN RUSSIAN]

408
00:31:04,590 --> 00:31:06,540
- THE CONCEPT OF CREOLE,
OR PEOPLE WHO ARE

409
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:09,510
OF MIXED SLAVIC
AND INDIGENOUS BACKGROUNDS,

410
00:31:09,530 --> 00:31:12,280
GOES BACK HUNDREDS OF YEARS
BEFORE ALASKA WAS EVEN

411
00:31:12,300 --> 00:31:17,120
DISCOVERED BY THE RUSSIANS.

412
00:31:17,140 --> 00:31:19,520
THE RUSSIANS WHO CAME
WERE REALLY NOT

413
00:31:19,540 --> 00:31:24,889
BLUE-EYED, BLOND-HAIRED
SLAVS FROM MOSCOW.

414
00:31:24,910 --> 00:31:28,360
THEY WERE PRIMARILY
MEN THEMSELVES OF MIXED

415
00:31:28,380 --> 00:31:31,800
RACIAL AND CULTURAL BACKGROUNDS.

416
00:31:31,820 --> 00:31:33,700
AND EVENTUALLY,
THESE MEN SETTLED

417
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:36,700
WITH THE ALEUT PEOPLE,
THE UNANGAN PEOPLE

418
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:40,410
IN THE ALEUTIAN CHAIN.

419
00:31:40,430 --> 00:31:43,140
THE CREOLES HAD AN ELEVATED
STATUS IN ALASKA.

420
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:45,80
THEY WERE THE MAINSTAY
OF THE COLONY.

421
00:31:45,100 --> 00:31:49,550
THE COLONY COULD NOT HAVE
FUNCTIONED WITHOUT THEM.

422
00:31:49,570 --> 00:31:53,250
THERE WASN'T AN ASSAULT
ON NATIVE LANGUAGE AND CULTURE,
PER SE,

423
00:31:53,270 --> 00:31:55,889
BUT THERE WAS
THE FOCUS ON TRAINING,

424
00:31:55,910 --> 00:31:58,160
ESPECIALLY THOSE
OF MIXED BACKGROUND,

425
00:31:58,180 --> 00:32:00,360
TO READ AND WRITE
AS WELL AS SPEAK

426
00:32:00,380 --> 00:32:01,930
IN AT LEAST 2 LANGUAGES,

427
00:32:01,950 --> 00:32:05,630
AND THEN THERE WERE
CREOLES WHO SPOKE 3 AND 4.

428
00:32:05,650 --> 00:32:08,230
THEY DIDN'T ABANDON THEIR
LANGUAGE AND THEIR CULTURE,

429
00:32:08,250 --> 00:32:13,770
BUT THEY ADDED TO IT.

430
00:32:13,790 --> 00:32:17,240
- THIS CREOLE CULTURE
WAS THROWN INTO TURMOIL

431
00:32:17,260 --> 00:32:21,10
WHEN THE UNITED STATES
PURCHASED ALASKA IN 1867

432
00:32:21,30 --> 00:32:25,450
FOR $7.2 MILLION.

433
00:32:25,470 --> 00:32:28,290
THE AMERICANS WERE
SO KEEN ON REAPING

434
00:32:28,310 --> 00:32:31,889
THE FINANCIAL REWARDS
OF THE FUR TRADE,

435
00:32:31,910 --> 00:32:33,960
AND THEY WERE JUST AS ADAMANT
ON IMPOSING

436
00:32:33,980 --> 00:32:37,830
AMERICAN LANGUAGE AND CUSTOMS.

437
00:32:37,850 --> 00:32:43,669
- AT THE TIME THE AMERICANS
ARRIVED IN ALASKA IN 1867,

438
00:32:43,690 --> 00:32:49,410
ALEUTS WERE CONSIDERED THE ELITE
NATIVE PEOPLE IN THE TERRITORY.

439
00:32:49,430 --> 00:32:55,280
TO BE AN ALEUT WAS TO BE
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

440
00:32:55,300 --> 00:32:57,379
PARTLY THAT WAS BECAUSE
ALEUTS HAD BECOME

441
00:32:57,400 --> 00:32:58,920
A VERY EDUCATED PEOPLE.

442
00:32:58,940 --> 00:33:04,390
THEY WERE LITERATE IN RUSSIAN,
LITERATE IN ALEUT.

443
00:33:04,410 --> 00:33:07,60
THEY HAD BEEN
MANAGERS, STOREKEEPERS.

444
00:33:07,80 --> 00:33:13,699
THEY HAD BEEN TEACHERS,
PRIESTS, DEACONS.

445
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:15,570
BUT WITH THE ARRIVAL
OF THE AMERICANS,

446
00:33:15,590 --> 00:33:22,439
THEY WERE NO LONGER ELIGIBLE
FOR ANY OF THOSE POSITIONS.

447
00:33:22,460 --> 00:33:26,10
THERE WAS A SENSE THAT
ALEUTS WERE INDIANS

448
00:33:26,30 --> 00:33:27,379
AND THAT THEY WERE
SAVAGE INDIANS,

449
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:29,280
BECAUSE THE INDIAN WARS
WERE STILL GOING ON

450
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:33,649
IN THE LOWER 48.

451
00:33:33,670 --> 00:33:35,350
IN ORDER FOR AN ALEUT TO BECOME

452
00:33:35,370 --> 00:33:37,919
A FULL PARTICIPANT
IN THE AMERICAN SYSTEM,

453
00:33:37,940 --> 00:33:40,190
HE OR SHE HAD TO
ESSENTIALLY ABANDON

454
00:33:40,210 --> 00:33:46,770
THEIR TIES
WITH THE ALEUT PEOPLE.

455
00:33:46,790 --> 00:33:51,670
- AFTER THE AMERICANS CAME,
THEY DISCOURAGED EVERYTHING
THAT WAS NATIVE.

456
00:33:51,690 --> 00:33:54,610
THEY DISCOURAGED
EVERYTHING THAT WAS ALEUT

457
00:33:54,630 --> 00:33:59,110
AND WANTED TO DO AWAY WITH IT.

458
00:33:59,130 --> 00:34:03,720
ABSOLUTELY YOU WERE NOT ALLOWED
TO SPEAK ALEUT IN SCHOOL.

459
00:34:03,740 --> 00:34:07,350
YOU WERE PUNISHED FOR THAT.

460
00:34:07,370 --> 00:34:08,719
- THE FEDERAL MARSHALS
GOT INVOLVED.

461
00:34:08,739 --> 00:34:13,290
THEY ARRESTED PARENTS.
THEY CLOSED SCHOOLS FORCIBLY.

462
00:34:13,310 --> 00:34:15,929
THE UNANGAN WERE BASICALLY
A PERSECUTED MINORITY

463
00:34:15,949 --> 00:34:17,429
IN THEIR OWN HOMELAND,
WHERE THEY WERE

464
00:34:17,449 --> 00:34:23,600
THE VAST MAJORITY
OF THE POPULATION.

465
00:34:23,620 --> 00:34:26,540
- MY PARENTS,
WHEN THEY WERE GROWING UP,

466
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:27,870
GOING TO GRADE SCHOOL,

467
00:34:27,889 --> 00:34:31,540
THEY WERE PUNISHED
FOR SPEAKING OUR LANGUAGE...

468
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:38,279
SO THEY DIDN'T WANT US
TO BE PUNISHED.

469
00:34:38,300 --> 00:34:42,290
MY PARENTS COULD SPEAK
TO EACH OTHER IN OUR LANGUAGE

470
00:34:42,310 --> 00:34:43,759
AND NONE OF US WOULD UNDERSTAND.

471
00:34:43,780 --> 00:34:48,330
IT WASN'T SPOKEN TO US.

472
00:34:48,350 --> 00:34:52,960
SO THERE WERE 9 OF US
IN MY FAMILY, 9 SIBLINGS,

473
00:34:52,980 --> 00:35:06,580
AND NONE OF US
PICKED UP THE LANGUAGE.

474
00:35:06,600 --> 00:35:10,680
UNANGAM TUNUU, THE LANGUAGE,
WASN'T THE ONLY THING

475
00:35:10,700 --> 00:35:15,450
SLOWLY DISAPPEARING FROM
THE ALEUTIANS ISLANDS.

476
00:35:15,470 --> 00:35:18,759
BY THE LATE 1760s, SEA OTTERS

477
00:35:18,780 --> 00:35:20,830
HAD BEEN BROUGHT
TO THE EDGE OF EXTINCTION

478
00:35:20,850 --> 00:35:25,500
BY THE DEMANDS
OF THIS FUR TRADE.

479
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:28,470
THE HUNTERS NEEDED
A NEW SOURCE OF FUR,

480
00:35:28,490 --> 00:35:33,140
AND THEY FOUND IT
IN THE NORTHERN FUR SEAL.

481
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:35,970
THE EASIEST WAY
TO CAPTURE THE FUR SEALS

482
00:35:35,990 --> 00:35:42,750
WAS AT THEIR BREEDING GROUNDS.

483
00:35:42,770 --> 00:35:47,490
IN 1786, A RUSSIAN NAVIGATOR,
GAVRIL PRIBYLOF,

484
00:35:47,510 --> 00:35:49,350
FOLLOWED THE NORTHERN FUR SEALS

485
00:35:49,370 --> 00:35:55,359
TO THEIR ROOKERIES
ON SAINT GEORGE ISLAND.

486
00:35:55,380 --> 00:35:58,460
THE RUSSIANS BEGAN BRINGING
UNANGAN MEN

487
00:35:58,480 --> 00:36:02,100
FROM THE ALEUTIAN CHAIN
TO HARVEST THE FIRST SEALS,

488
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:05,940
AND BY 1867,
WHEN THE AMERICANS TOOK OVER,

489
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:13,850
THERE WERE SIZABLE SETTLEMENTS
ON BOTH ISLANDS.

490
00:36:13,870 --> 00:36:17,620
IN 1882, MY GREAT-GRANDFATHER
INNOKENTY

491
00:36:17,640 --> 00:36:27,730
MOVED TO SAINT GEORGE ISLAND
TO SERVE AS THE PARISH PRIEST.

492
00:36:27,750 --> 00:36:30,530
HE HAD TO PETITION
THE ALASKA COMMERCIAL COMPANY

493
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:34,200
FOR YEARS TO GET THEM TO ALLOW
HIS SON DMITRI

494
00:36:34,220 --> 00:36:39,169
TO RELOCATE, AS WELL.

495
00:36:39,190 --> 00:36:55,90
[GULLS SQUAWKING]

496
00:36:55,110 --> 00:36:58,220
THIS IS THE VILLAGE
OF SAINT GEORGE.

497
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:01,990
THIS IS WHERE I WAS BORN...

498
00:37:02,10 --> 00:37:05,200
AND RIGHT OVER HERE BEHIND ME

499
00:37:05,220 --> 00:37:08,770
IS THE HOME OF MY GRANDMOTHER
AND GRANDFATHER,

500
00:37:08,790 --> 00:37:12,470
MY MOM'S PARENTS, AND SO
FROM THE TIME I WAS BORN

501
00:37:12,490 --> 00:37:15,910
TILL I WAS ABOUT 4 YEARS OLD,
I SPENT A LOT OF TIME

502
00:37:15,930 --> 00:37:21,350
COMING OVER HERE
TO MY GRANDMOTHER'S HOUSE...

503
00:37:21,370 --> 00:37:26,650
AND WHEN I COME HERE, I ALWAYS
STILL FEEL QUITE AT HOME,

504
00:37:26,670 --> 00:37:30,20
EVEN IF IT'S BEEN A FEW DECADES
SINCE I'VE ACTUALLY SPENT

505
00:37:30,40 --> 00:37:42,870
MORE THAN A FEW DAYS HERE.

506
00:37:42,890 --> 00:37:46,240
WHEN YOU COME HERE
TO SAINT GEORGE,

507
00:37:46,260 --> 00:37:48,910
EVERYTHING IS NESTLED
ALL TOGETHER,

508
00:37:48,930 --> 00:37:58,319
THE VILLAGE WITH THE BIRD CLIFFS
AND THE FUR SEALS.

509
00:37:58,340 --> 00:38:15,430
IT'S ALL JUST RIGHT HERE
AT THE DOORSTEP OF THE VILLAGE.

510
00:38:15,450 --> 00:38:20,910
MY GREAT-GRANDFATHER,
REVEREND INNOKENTY LESTENKOF,

511
00:38:20,930 --> 00:38:26,9
WAS THE FIRST LESTENKOF
ON THE PRIBILOF ISLANDS,

512
00:38:26,30 --> 00:38:30,950
AND HE SERVED THE PARISH HERE
IN THE LATE 1800s,

513
00:38:30,970 --> 00:38:36,390
AND HERE IS WHERE HE IS BURIED--

514
00:38:36,410 --> 00:38:51,370
REVEREND INNOKENTY
MIKHAILOVICH LESTENKOV.

515
00:38:51,390 --> 00:38:57,680
IN THE BELIEF OF UNANGAN PEOPLE,
OUR LIFE IS A VISIT.

516
00:38:57,700 --> 00:38:59,779
WE DON'T HAVE A WORD FOR DEATH.

517
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:03,980
WE USE A WORD THAT ACTUALLY
TRANSLATES INTO ENGLISH

518
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:18,830
AS "DONE VISITING THIS LAND."

519
00:39:18,850 --> 00:39:21,630
WHEN THE AMERICANS TOOK OVER
THE FUR INDUSTRY

520
00:39:21,650 --> 00:39:24,770
ON SAINT PAUL
AND SAINT GEORGE ISLANDS,

521
00:39:24,790 --> 00:39:30,509
THEY BEGAN KEEPING
METICULOUS RECORDS.

522
00:39:30,530 --> 00:39:34,280
PART OF MY JOB AT THE TRIBAL
GOVERNMENT OF SAINT PAUL

523
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:37,120
IS TO LOOK AT
THESE OLD ARCHIVES,

524
00:39:37,140 --> 00:39:41,750
SO MY COWORKER
SAMANTHA ZACHAROF AND I

525
00:39:41,770 --> 00:39:44,390
HAVE SPENT MANY HOURS
PORING OVER THESE RECORDS.

526
00:39:44,410 --> 00:39:49,629
OH, I DIDN'T KNOW
THIS WENT BACK THAT FAR.

527
00:39:49,650 --> 00:39:51,800
BOTH SAINT PAUL
AND SAINT GEORGE ISLANDS

528
00:39:51,820 --> 00:39:56,130
WERE RUN LIKE COMPANY TOWNS.

529
00:39:56,150 --> 00:40:03,910
THE UNANGAN WORKERS
WERE WARDS OF THE STATE.

530
00:40:03,930 --> 00:40:08,80
- WE BECAME IN A STATE OF
SERVITUDE TO THE U.S. GOVERNMENT

531
00:40:08,100 --> 00:40:12,450
AS THE ONLY CAPTIVE LABOR FORCE
OF THE AMERICAN GOVERNMENT

532
00:40:12,470 --> 00:40:18,790
IN THE ENTIRE HISTORY
OF THE UNITED STATES.

533
00:40:18,810 --> 00:40:21,730
- EVERY ASPECT
OF THE FUR INDUSTRY OPERATED

534
00:40:21,750 --> 00:40:26,460
UNDER GOVERNMENT SUPERVISION,

535
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:28,700
AND WORKERS WERE GIVEN
ALLOTMENTS

536
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:33,509
THAT THEY USED
TO MAKE PURCHASES.

537
00:40:33,530 --> 00:40:39,240
EVERY TRANSACTION WAS RECORDED
DOWN TO THE LAST PENNY.

538
00:40:39,260 --> 00:40:43,980
SO FOR SOMEONE IN 1898
ON MARCH 26

539
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:46,820
TO PURCHASE TEA, SUGAR, MILK,
BUTTER, FLOUR, SOUP,

540
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:50,460
TOBACCO, MATCHES, FRUIT,

541
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:54,390
AND--I DON'T KNOW WHAT THAT IS--
HANDKERCHIEFS,

542
00:40:54,410 --> 00:41:02,129
ONE PAIR OF BABY SHOES--
75 CENTS.

543
00:41:02,150 --> 00:41:05,640
MOST PEOPLE DON'T EVEN KNOW
THAT THE UNITED STATES

544
00:41:05,660 --> 00:41:08,940
HAD A FUR SEAL INDUSTRY,

545
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:13,80
MUCH LESS THE CONDITIONS
WITH WHICH THE WORKFORCE,

546
00:41:13,100 --> 00:41:18,580
THE UNANGAN PEOPLE,
HAD TO LIVE WITH.

547
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:22,89
- ALASKA WAS PURCHASED
FOR $7.2 MILLION.

548
00:41:22,110 --> 00:41:25,390
THE PRIBILOF ISLANDS ALONE
HAVE PROBABLY PAID

549
00:41:25,410 --> 00:41:27,660
FOR THE STATE OF ALASKA

550
00:41:27,680 --> 00:41:30,859
AT LEAST 10 TIMES OVER.

551
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:33,730
I KNOW IT'S MORE THAN THAT.

552
00:41:33,750 --> 00:41:37,900
DID WE GET OUR FAIR SHARE? NO.

553
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:40,710
IF YOU GET PAID 25 CENTS A SKIN
WHEN THAT SKIN

554
00:41:40,730 --> 00:41:49,80
IS WORTH HUNDREDS OF DOLLARS,
I DON'T THINK SO.

555
00:41:49,100 --> 00:41:50,950
- WHAT'S IN HERE?

556
00:41:50,970 --> 00:41:53,990
- THIS IS JUST
THEIR ORDER FORMS FOR SEARS.

557
00:41:54,10 --> 00:41:55,590
- OK.

558
00:41:55,610 --> 00:41:57,890
READING SOME OF THIS STUFF,
I HAVE TO STAND UP

559
00:41:57,910 --> 00:42:05,129
AND JUST TAKE A DEEP BREATH
BECAUSE I WANT TO GET ANGRY.

560
00:42:05,150 --> 00:42:07,100
THAT'S THE HARD PART.

561
00:42:07,120 --> 00:42:10,600
HOW DO YOU HAVE A PIECE
OF HISTORY BE KNOWN AND BE TOLD

562
00:42:10,620 --> 00:42:13,940
WITHOUT MAKING
THE NEXT GENERATION ANGRY?

563
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:18,110
- THIS IS PART OF HISTORY,
NO MATTER HOW IT MAKES YOU FEEL.

564
00:42:18,130 --> 00:42:20,140
- YEAH.

565
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:23,279
HOW DO YOU HAVE IT GO FORWARD
INTO THE FUTURE

566
00:42:23,300 --> 00:42:30,560
AND BE USED SO AS
NOT TO REPEAT ITSELF?

567
00:42:30,580 --> 00:42:39,460
I THINK IT AFFIRMS THE NEED
FOR THIS HISTORY TO BE KNOWN.

568
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:54,710
IT'S NOT JUST OUR HISTORY.
IT'S THE HISTORY OF THIS NATION.

569
00:42:54,730 --> 00:42:56,780
BOTH MY FATHER AND MY MOTHER

570
00:42:56,800 --> 00:43:00,20
WERE BORN
ON SAINT GEORGE ISLAND.

571
00:43:00,40 --> 00:43:05,590
MY FATHER, MICHAEL LESTENKOF,
WAS BORN IN 1913.

572
00:43:05,610 --> 00:43:11,30
MY MOTHER STEFANIDA LEKANOF
WAS BORN IN 1919.

573
00:43:11,50 --> 00:43:17,670
IN 1938, THEY GOT MARRIED.

574
00:43:17,690 --> 00:43:20,440
LIKE ALL THE MEN
ON SAINT GEORGE ISLAND,

575
00:43:20,460 --> 00:43:26,110
MY FATHER WORKED
IN THE FUR SEAL INDUSTRY.

576
00:43:26,130 --> 00:43:28,450
THAT'S HIM TAKING
A CIGARETTE BREAK

577
00:43:28,470 --> 00:43:31,649
IN FRONT OF THE SEAL PLANT.

578
00:43:31,670 --> 00:43:33,550
- THAT'S IT. THAT'S IT.
A LITTLE MORE. A LITTLE MORE.

579
00:43:33,570 --> 00:43:35,350
THAT'S IT. COME ON.

580
00:43:35,370 --> 00:43:38,490
- ALL IN A DAY'S WORK, THE FIRST
SEAL HARVEST WOULD BEGIN

581
00:43:38,510 --> 00:43:44,730
WITH AN EARLY-MORNING ROUNDUP
FROM THE BEACH.

582
00:43:44,750 --> 00:43:48,570
PLACING THEMSELVES BETWEEN
THE SEALS AND THE SEA,

583
00:43:48,590 --> 00:43:54,740
SHOUTING AND WHISTLING,
THEY DRIVE THE SEALS INLAND.

584
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:59,510
USING LONG HICKORY STICKS,
THEY DIVIDE OUT A POD

585
00:43:59,530 --> 00:44:02,310
OF ABOUT 6 TO 12 SEALS.

586
00:44:02,330 --> 00:44:04,220
- YEAH. A LITTLE MORE.
THAT'S IT.

587
00:44:04,240 --> 00:44:07,589
- EACH SEAL IS DELIVERED
A SINGLE BLOW TO THE HEAD,

588
00:44:07,610 --> 00:44:11,90
WHICH STUNS THEM...

589
00:44:11,110 --> 00:44:21,730
AND WITH A KNIFE PIERCING
TO THE HEART, THEY ARE KILLED.

590
00:44:21,750 --> 00:44:25,100
THE WASHHOUSE BUILDING
ON SAINT GEORGE ISLAND

591
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:28,509
IS THE ONLY REMAINING EVIDENCE
OF WHAT WAS ONCE

592
00:44:28,530 --> 00:44:32,210
A VERY BUSY FUR SEAL INDUSTRY.

593
00:44:32,230 --> 00:44:34,850
- ONCE THE FUR SEAL PROCESS...

594
00:44:34,870 --> 00:44:37,49
- ANTHONY MERCULIEF
IS ONE OF THE LAST PEOPLE

595
00:44:37,70 --> 00:44:41,90
ON SAINT GEORGE ISLAND TO HAVE
WORKED AT THE SEAL PLANT.

596
00:44:41,110 --> 00:44:45,360
- THE DUMP TRUCKS WOULD BRING
THE PELTS TO THIS PLATFORM HERE.

597
00:44:45,380 --> 00:44:47,960
THE WINDOWS WERE OPEN,
AND THE SEAL SKINS

598
00:44:47,980 --> 00:44:51,160
WERE THROWN INSIDE THE TANKS
THAT ARE IN THERE

599
00:44:51,180 --> 00:44:53,870
THAT ARE FILLED WITH SALTWATER.

600
00:44:53,890 --> 00:44:56,970
- SO THIS WOULD BE
THE SKIN HOUSE OR THE WASHHOUSE?

601
00:44:56,990 --> 00:44:58,270
- WASHHOUSE. YEAH.

602
00:44:58,290 --> 00:45:00,70
THIS IS WHERE THE SKINS
WERE BROUGHT IN

603
00:45:00,90 --> 00:45:02,240
THROUGH THE WINDOWS OVER THERE.

604
00:45:02,260 --> 00:45:04,480
THIS WAS FILLED UP
WITH SALTWATER,

605
00:45:04,500 --> 00:45:08,380
AND THE SKINS WERE PUT IN HERE
AND SOAKED OVERNIGHT.

606
00:45:08,400 --> 00:45:11,380
- DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY SKINS
THEY WOULD BE ABLE TO FIT IN?

607
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:19,420
- IN EACH TANK,
PROBABLY 100 OR MORE.

608
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:21,60
THEY HAD AN OVERHEAD TROLLEY

609
00:45:21,80 --> 00:45:23,90
THAT HUNG FROM
THIS TRACK RIGHT HERE.

610
00:45:23,110 --> 00:45:25,360
THEY WOULD FILL THE THING
WITH SEAL SKINS

611
00:45:25,380 --> 00:45:27,670
AND HAUL THEM DOWN
THROUGH THIS TRACK

612
00:45:27,690 --> 00:45:29,930
TO THAT FAR END OF THE BUILDING,

613
00:45:29,950 --> 00:45:31,839
WHERE THEY WERE PUT
ON THE TABLES

614
00:45:31,860 --> 00:45:38,180
AND GIVEN TO THE BLUBBER PEOPLE
TO BLUBBER THEM.

615
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:42,80
- THEN FROM IN HERE
AND ON THESE TRACKS,

616
00:45:42,100 --> 00:45:44,750
IS THIS HOW SKINS WERE BROUGHT
INTO THIS ROOM?

617
00:45:44,770 --> 00:45:46,550
- RIGHT.

618
00:45:46,570 --> 00:45:48,490
- AND THIS WAS
THE BLUBBERY SHOP, HUH?

619
00:45:48,510 --> 00:45:49,850
- YEAH.

620
00:45:49,870 --> 00:45:52,259
- AND WHAT ARE THESE TABLES FOR?

621
00:45:52,280 --> 00:45:55,160
- THIS IS WHERE SKINS
WERE STACKED.

622
00:45:55,180 --> 00:45:57,500
- SO HOPEFULLY,
YOU DIDN'T HAVE A BIG PILE.

623
00:45:57,520 --> 00:45:59,960
- RIGHT, AND SMALL SKINS.

624
00:45:59,980 --> 00:46:02,400
- YEAH. OH, OK, SIZE.

625
00:46:02,420 --> 00:46:03,940
- THE EASY ONES.

626
00:46:03,960 --> 00:46:06,240
THE BIG ONES WERE STRINGY
AND HARD TO BLUBBER.

627
00:46:06,260 --> 00:46:09,270
- OH, OK.
SO YOU BLUBBERED HERE, TOO.

628
00:46:09,290 --> 00:46:11,440
- YEAH.
- YEAH?

629
00:46:11,460 --> 00:46:13,540
- YOU WOULD REACH OVER
AND GRAB A SKIN,

630
00:46:13,560 --> 00:46:15,210
PUT IT ON THE BEAM
FUR SIDE UP,

631
00:46:15,230 --> 00:46:16,550
AND YOU'D GRAB A KNIFE
FROM HERE,

632
00:46:16,570 --> 00:46:18,420
CUT THE EARS OFF,
CUT A LITTLE BIT

633
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:22,450
OF THE SKIN
AROUND THE ARM HOLES.

634
00:46:22,470 --> 00:46:24,990
THEN YOU TAKE THE SKIN
AND TURN IT AROUND

635
00:46:25,10 --> 00:46:28,60
WITH THE BLUBBER SIDE UP
AND SCRAPE THE BLUBBER OFF.

636
00:46:28,80 --> 00:46:29,490
THEN WHEN YOU GOT DONE
WITH THAT,

637
00:46:29,510 --> 00:46:34,30
YOU FLIP IT OVER
AND DO THE OTHER SIDE.

638
00:46:34,50 --> 00:46:38,200
- IN 2000, I CAME OVER WITH
MY DAD INTO THE SEAL PLANT HERE,

639
00:46:38,220 --> 00:46:39,899
AND WHEN HE COUNTED DOWN,
HE SAID,

640
00:46:39,920 --> 00:46:42,570
"THIS IS BLUBBER BEAM
NUMBER 13,"

641
00:46:42,590 --> 00:46:45,580
AND HE SAID, "NO ONE WANTED
TO BLUBBER HERE

642
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:48,509
"BECAUSE 13
WAS AN UNLUCKY NUMBER,

643
00:46:48,530 --> 00:46:52,180
"BUT SINCE I WAS BORN
ON OCTOBER 13, 1913,

644
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:57,460
IT'S MY LUCKY NUMBER, SO THIS
IS WHERE I BLUBBERED PELTS."

645
00:46:57,480 --> 00:47:00,360
HE'D SAY, "I WAS BORN
ON THE 13th HOUR, TOO,"

646
00:47:00,380 --> 00:47:01,790
BUT I DON'T THINK HE WAS.

647
00:47:01,810 --> 00:47:04,100
HE JUST THREW THAT IN
FOR THE STORY.

648
00:47:04,120 --> 00:47:21,250
[BOTH LAUGH]

649
00:47:21,270 --> 00:47:24,480
IN 1941, THERE WERE
ABOUT 500 UNANGAN

650
00:47:24,500 --> 00:47:28,650
LIVING ON SAINT GEORGE
AND SAINT PAUL ISLANDS,

651
00:47:28,670 --> 00:47:34,430
BUT ONE YEAR LATER,
THERE WOULD BE NONE.

652
00:47:34,450 --> 00:47:39,259
WORLD WAR II SHATTERED LIFE
ON THE PRIBILOF ISLANDS.

653
00:47:39,280 --> 00:47:43,270
- WE USED TO HEAR THE PLANES
GOING OVER THE ISLAND.

654
00:47:43,290 --> 00:47:48,910
THE BLACKOUTS STARTED RIGHT
AFTER PEARL HARBOR WAS BOMBED.

655
00:47:48,930 --> 00:47:50,980
- MY MOTHER-IN-LAW
MARY BOURDUKOFSKY

656
00:47:51,000 --> 00:47:52,940
WAS A YOUNG WOMAN
WITH YOUNG CHILDREN

657
00:47:52,960 --> 00:47:54,910
WHEN WORLD WAR II BROKE OUT.

658
00:47:54,930 --> 00:47:57,250
SAME RIGHT HERE.
- MM-HMM.

659
00:47:57,270 --> 00:48:00,350
ALL THE WINDOWS AT NIGHT,
YOU HAMMER A BLANKET

660
00:48:00,370 --> 00:48:04,560
TO MAKE IT DARK, NO LIGHTS,

661
00:48:04,580 --> 00:48:06,220
NO KIND OF A LIGHT,
AND YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED

662
00:48:06,240 --> 00:48:13,529
TO EVEN SMOKE CIGARETTE
OUTSIDE OR NOTHING.

663
00:48:13,550 --> 00:48:21,540
- IN JUNE 1942, THE JAPANESE
BOMBED THE HARBOR AT UNALASKA.

664
00:48:21,560 --> 00:48:26,840
THEY INVADED THE ISLANDS
OF ATTU AND KISKA...

665
00:48:26,860 --> 00:48:32,350
AND THEY TOOK
AMERICAN CITIZENS CAPTIVE.

666
00:48:32,370 --> 00:48:34,790
- JUNE 1942.

667
00:48:34,810 --> 00:48:36,990
THE NEWS ABOUT DUTCH HARBOR
BEING BOMBED

668
00:48:37,10 --> 00:48:40,890
AT 6 A.M. REACHED US YESTERDAY.

669
00:48:40,910 --> 00:48:44,299
NEXT CAME NEWS OF ATTU.

670
00:48:44,320 --> 00:48:47,270
THE WAR BECAME
TOO HORRIBLY REAL.

671
00:48:47,290 --> 00:48:49,300
IT SEEMED SENSIBLE TO PREPARE,

672
00:48:49,320 --> 00:48:51,470
SO THE FIRST AND ONLY
AIR RAID SHELTER

673
00:48:51,490 --> 00:48:55,669
IS BEING ERECTED ON SAINT PAUL.

674
00:48:55,690 --> 00:48:57,510
WE APPEALED TO
THE GOVERNMENT AGENT

675
00:48:57,530 --> 00:49:01,650
TO TAKE SOME ACTION
FOR THE COMMUNITY'S SAFETY.

676
00:49:01,670 --> 00:49:10,190
WE BEGGED HIM TO EVACUATE
THE WOMEN AND CHILDREN AT LEAST.

677
00:49:10,210 --> 00:49:13,860
- THE UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT
ORDERED A COMPLETE EVACUATION

678
00:49:13,880 --> 00:49:20,60
OF ALL UNANGAN FROM THE ALEUTIAN
AND PRIBILOF ISLANDS.

679
00:49:20,80 --> 00:49:23,200
YOU DIDN'T KNOW BEFOREHAND...

680
00:49:23,220 --> 00:49:25,169
- NO. WE DIDN'T KNOW.

681
00:49:25,190 --> 00:49:26,800
- THAT YOU WERE BEING EVACUATED?

682
00:49:26,820 --> 00:49:29,540
- NO. WE DIDN'T KNOW.
- WHEN DID YOU FIND OUT?

683
00:49:29,560 --> 00:49:32,80
- IT WAS SUNDAY AFTERNOON,

684
00:49:32,100 --> 00:49:38,880
AND THEY USED TO HAVE A BIG
BALL GAME GOING ON ON SUNDAYS.

685
00:49:38,900 --> 00:49:42,620
THAT SUNDAY HAPPENED TO BE
A BEAUTIFUL DAY,

686
00:49:42,640 --> 00:49:47,629
AND MY HUSBAND WAS A BALLPLAYER,
AND HE WENT OUT, BUT I WAS HOME.

687
00:49:47,650 --> 00:49:50,90
I HAD A LITTLE,
3-MONTHS-OLD BABY

688
00:49:50,110 --> 00:49:56,600
AND A TWO-YEAR-OLD LITTLE BOY.

689
00:49:56,620 --> 00:50:00,810
SO I WAS WASHING DIAPERS
BY WASHBOARD, YOU KNOW?

690
00:50:00,830 --> 00:50:03,509
I DIDN'T HAVE NO
WASHING MACHINE,

691
00:50:03,530 --> 00:50:10,250
AND THE BIG TRANSPORT LANDED
OVER THERE IN EAST LANDING.

692
00:50:10,270 --> 00:50:13,280
PEOPLE WERE JUST PUZZLED,
WHAT WAS GOING ON,

693
00:50:13,300 --> 00:50:16,350
AND THEN MY HUSBAND CAME
RUNNING HOME TO TELL ME

694
00:50:16,370 --> 00:50:19,220
THAT THEY'RE TAKING EVERYBODY.

695
00:50:19,240 --> 00:50:23,160
SAID, "THEY TELL US TO TAKE JUST
WHAT YOU HAVE ON YOUR BACK

696
00:50:23,180 --> 00:50:26,460
AND CHANGE OF CLOTHES.
THAT'S ALL,"

697
00:50:26,480 --> 00:50:32,670
AND WE DIDN'T HAD NO SUITCASES
BECAUSE WE NEVER TRAVEL,

698
00:50:32,690 --> 00:50:37,540
SO I START FILLING UP CLEAN
50-POUND FLOUR SACKS

699
00:50:37,560 --> 00:50:40,340
I HAVE WITH MY CHILDREN CLOTHES,

700
00:50:40,360 --> 00:50:47,690
AND A CARDBOARD BOX I HAVE,
I FILLED THAT ONE, TOO.

701
00:50:47,710 --> 00:50:55,830
THEY WALKED ALL THE WAY
TO EAST LANDING HERE.

702
00:50:55,850 --> 00:51:00,430
IT WAS SO SAD.
WOMEN WERE CRYING.

703
00:51:00,450 --> 00:51:02,629
ELDERS WERE CRYING,

704
00:51:02,650 --> 00:51:10,880
AND PEOPLE CARRY A SACK
OF THEIR CLOTHES.

705
00:51:10,900 --> 00:51:14,80
- EVERYONE WAS EVACUATED--

706
00:51:14,100 --> 00:51:18,680
MARY'S FAMILY,
MY FATHER AND MY MOTHER,

707
00:51:18,700 --> 00:51:22,589
MY OLDER SISTER AND BROTHER.

708
00:51:22,610 --> 00:51:29,190
THEY WERE ALL TAKEN TO A CAMP
IN SOUTHEASTERN ALASKA,

709
00:51:29,210 --> 00:51:35,370
TO A PLACE CALLED FUNTER BAY.

710
00:51:35,390 --> 00:51:40,839
- THE HUNGER AND THE COLD,

711
00:51:40,860 --> 00:51:46,810
THAT REALLY GETS US
IN FUNTER BAY.

712
00:51:46,830 --> 00:51:51,350
I HAD TO DRESS MY LITTLE KIDS
WITH WHATEVER THEY HAD.

713
00:51:51,370 --> 00:51:57,220
ALL THEIR THINGS GOT WORN OUT.
THEY GOT SMALL.

714
00:51:57,240 --> 00:52:02,330
MY LITTLE BOY HAD NO SHOES,
AND IT'S BARE FLOOR,

715
00:52:02,350 --> 00:52:05,960
AND THE MEMORIES
COME BACK TO ME.

716
00:52:05,980 --> 00:52:10,400
- MM-HMM.
- YEAH.

717
00:52:10,420 --> 00:52:13,670
WHAT THEY ISSUE US IS POWDERED--

718
00:52:13,690 --> 00:52:17,370
POWDERED EGGS, POWDERED MILK.

719
00:52:17,390 --> 00:52:23,80
WE HAD NO STOVE TO COOK, ANYWAY.

720
00:52:23,100 --> 00:52:27,250
THERE WAS NO RUNNING WATER,
NO BATHS, NO TOILETS,

721
00:52:27,270 --> 00:52:30,960
EXCEPT FOR ONE OVER THE BAY.

722
00:52:30,980 --> 00:52:33,490
YOU HAVE TO WALK ON A PLANK.

723
00:52:33,510 --> 00:52:35,60
- THERE WAS JUST THE HOLE.

724
00:52:35,80 --> 00:52:40,200
- YEAH. THE WASTE JUST GOES
IN THE BAY...

725
00:52:40,220 --> 00:52:43,770
AND THERE WERE FISH SWIMMING
AROUND, AND WE COULDN'T EAT IT.

726
00:52:43,790 --> 00:52:46,270
HOW COULD WE?

727
00:52:46,290 --> 00:52:53,9
AND THE BABIES WERE SICKLY--
COLD, SORES, IMPETIGOS...

728
00:52:53,30 --> 00:52:57,410
AND WE WERE INFESTED WITH LICE.

729
00:52:57,430 --> 00:53:00,120
ALL THAT 2 1/2 YEARS,
WE WERE THERE

730
00:53:00,140 --> 00:53:12,460
CLEANING OUR HEADS
EVERY NIGHT SOMETIMES.

731
00:53:12,480 --> 00:53:15,200
I ALWAYS SAY, "I HOPE
IT NEVER HAPPENS AGAIN."

732
00:53:15,220 --> 00:53:23,209
- YEAH.

733
00:53:23,230 --> 00:53:26,410
- TOGETHER, WE TRY TO
REMEMBER WHAT OUR PARENTS

734
00:53:26,430 --> 00:53:31,720
AND GRANDPARENTS WENT
THROUGH DURING THE WAR.

735
00:53:31,740 --> 00:53:35,120
SUFFERING THAT DIDN'T END
WHEN PEOPLE CAME BACK FROM

736
00:53:35,140 --> 00:53:40,120
FUNTER BAY.

737
00:53:40,140 --> 00:53:43,460
OUR PARENTS AND OUR
GRANDPARENTS CAME HOME TO FIND

738
00:53:43,480 --> 00:53:46,160
THEIR HOUSES RANSACKED.

739
00:53:46,180 --> 00:53:49,529
[PRIEST RECITING SCRIPTURE]

740
00:53:49,550 --> 00:53:53,670
AMERICAN SOLDIERS HAD
TAKEN EVERYTHING OF VALUE,

741
00:53:53,690 --> 00:53:59,40
EVEN ICONS FROM OUR CHURCHES.

742
00:53:59,60 --> 00:54:04,480
BUT THE DEEPEST LOSS WAS OF
THOSE WHO NEVER RETURNED.

743
00:54:04,500 --> 00:54:23,370
BECAUSE THEY DIED
AT FUNTER BAY.

744
00:54:23,390 --> 00:54:27,400
IN 1960, I WAS BORN
ON SAINT GEORGE ISLAND,

745
00:54:27,420 --> 00:54:33,140
THE 8TH OF 9 CHILDREN.

746
00:54:33,160 --> 00:54:37,109
AND WHEN I WAS 3 YEARS OLD,
MY DAD FOLLOWED IN MY GREAT

747
00:54:37,130 --> 00:54:40,420
GRANDFATHER INNOKENTY'S
FOOTSTEPS, AND HE BECAME

748
00:54:40,440 --> 00:54:45,390
AN ORTHODOX PRIEST.

749
00:54:45,410 --> 00:54:49,359
IN 1964, MY FATHER WAS
TRANSFERRED TO SERVE THE

750
00:54:49,380 --> 00:54:55,000
PARISH OF SAINT PAUL ISLAND,
SO WE MOVED THERE.

751
00:54:55,20 --> 00:55:01,540
[YELLING, METALLIC CLANGING]

752
00:55:01,560 --> 00:55:04,940
THE 1970's WOULD LEAD
TO DIFFICULT TIMES

753
00:55:04,960 --> 00:55:09,380
FOR THE COMMERCIAL
FUR SEAL INDUSTRY.

754
00:55:09,400 --> 00:55:13,180
- WITH MAN'S DOMINION
OVER ANIMALS--AS GOD KNOWS,

755
00:55:13,200 --> 00:55:15,450
THAT BIBLE IS
QUOTED TO US ENOUGH--

756
00:55:15,470 --> 00:55:17,759
WITH THAT GOES RESPONSIBILITY.

757
00:55:17,780 --> 00:55:21,590
- ON JANUARY, 1970, PRESIDENT
NIXON PROMISED PEACE WITH

758
00:55:21,610 --> 00:55:24,630
NATURE, AND I QUOTE
THAT "PEACE WITH NATURE."

759
00:55:24,650 --> 00:55:28,470
AND WHAT BETTER PLACE TO
START THAN TO END THE MASSACRE

760
00:55:28,490 --> 00:55:31,200
OF SEALS BY
GOVERNMENT EMPLOYEES?

761
00:55:31,220 --> 00:55:33,299
- IT'S FOR NOTHING EXCEPT
A LUXURY PRODUCT.

762
00:55:33,320 --> 00:55:36,870
IT'S STRICTLY TO PLEASE THE
VANITY OF SOME WOMEN THAT

763
00:55:36,890 --> 00:55:40,609
THESE SEALS ARE BEING CLUBBED
AND BLED AND STUCK AND SKINNED.

764
00:55:40,630 --> 00:55:42,880
- WE ARE OPPOSED TO THE
UNNECESSARY KILLING OF ANY

765
00:55:42,900 --> 00:55:46,50
ANIMAL, AND I THINK IT'S OUR
RESPONSIBILITY TO TAKE A COLD,

766
00:55:46,70 --> 00:55:51,420
HARD LOOK AT WHAT WE'RE DOING.

767
00:55:51,440 --> 00:55:54,660
- IT WAS AN INDISCRIMINATE
OUTRAGE, I THINK, THAT WAS

768
00:55:54,680 --> 00:55:58,859
FOCUSED PRIMARILY
ON OUR PEOPLE.

769
00:55:58,880 --> 00:56:02,670
WE WERE GETTING HATE MAIL FROM
ALL OVER THE WORLD FROM PEOPLE

770
00:56:02,690 --> 00:56:05,770
WHO WERE BEING MISLED BY
CERTAIN KINDS OF ANIMAL RIGHTS

771
00:56:05,790 --> 00:56:08,770
GROUPS FIGHTING AGAINST THE
TAKING OF FUR SEALS FOR THEIR

772
00:56:08,790 --> 00:56:16,150
PELTS BY THE U.S. GOVERNMENT.

773
00:56:16,170 --> 00:56:19,680
- TIME AND TIME AGAIN, WE'VE
BEEN THE ONES TO HAVE TO STAND

774
00:56:19,700 --> 00:56:26,560
UP TO IGNORANCE ABOUT
THE FUR SEALS.

775
00:56:26,580 --> 00:56:31,29
THE RUSSIANS AND THE AMERICANS
WANTED TO TAKE ALL THE FUR

776
00:56:31,50 --> 00:56:35,430
SEALS FOR A QUICK PROFIT.

777
00:56:35,450 --> 00:56:40,970
WE HAD BEEN THE ONES TO SAY THE
HARVEST HAD TO BE SUSTAINABLE.

778
00:56:40,990 --> 00:56:45,779
NOW, OUTSIDERS
HAD A NEW DEMAND--

779
00:56:45,800 --> 00:56:50,410
STOP THE HARVEST ALTOGETHER.

780
00:56:50,430 --> 00:56:54,520
- WE HAD NO PLANS FOR AN
ALTERNATIVE ECONOMIC BASE,

781
00:56:54,540 --> 00:56:56,720
SO UNCERTAINTY WAS
THERE, DEPRESSION SET

782
00:56:56,740 --> 00:57:00,160
IN ON A COMMUNITY-WIDE BASIS,
AND WE BEGAN TO HAVE ONE

783
00:57:00,180 --> 00:57:03,330
SERIES OF TRAGIC
EVENTS AFTER ANOTHER.

784
00:57:03,350 --> 00:57:08,630
BETWEEN 1982 AND 1983, WE
HAD 100 DOCUMENTED SUICIDE

785
00:57:08,650 --> 00:57:13,770
ATTEMPTS, 4 SUICIDES, 3 MURDERS.

786
00:57:13,790 --> 00:57:17,779
DEFINITELY, WE SAW THE EFFECTS
OF A GOVERNMENT-RUN COMPANY

787
00:57:17,800 --> 00:57:20,840
TOWN WHEN THE GOVERNMENT
DECIDES TO PULL OUT.

788
00:57:20,860 --> 00:57:22,850
WE WERE LITERALLY
PLANNING ONE-WAY TICKETS

789
00:57:22,870 --> 00:57:29,950
FOR PEOPLE OFF THE ISLAND.

790
00:57:29,970 --> 00:57:40,930
[MOTOR RUNS]

791
00:57:40,950 --> 00:57:44,740
- IN 1983, WE SAW THE
END OF THE COMMERCIAL

792
00:57:44,760 --> 00:57:49,170
FUR SEAL INDUSTRY.

793
00:57:49,190 --> 00:57:53,140
SO YOU WOULD SUSPECT YOU
WOULD SEE THE NUMBER OF

794
00:57:53,160 --> 00:57:58,80
FUR SEALS INCREASE.

795
00:57:58,100 --> 00:58:05,560
EVERYBODY ASSUMES THE
POPULATION IS GOING UP.

796
00:58:05,580 --> 00:58:15,970
SOMETHING IS HAPPENING.

797
00:58:15,990 --> 00:58:23,410
THIS HISTORICALLY WAS
A FUR SEAL ROOKERY.

798
00:58:23,430 --> 00:58:28,580
WHEN THE RUSSIAN FUR TRADERS
FIRST CAME HERE, THE ROCKY

799
00:58:28,600 --> 00:58:33,580
AREAS ON TOLSTOY ROOKERY
WERE COMPLETELY COVERED

800
00:58:33,600 --> 00:58:40,20
WITH FUR SEALS.

801
00:58:40,40 --> 00:58:44,930
IT'S REALLY HARD TO GIVE
PEOPLE AN IDEA WHAT A FEW

802
00:58:44,950 --> 00:58:50,669
MILLION FUR SEALS
WOULD LOOK LIKE.

803
00:58:50,690 --> 00:58:53,870
PEOPLE COME HERE NOW AND THEY
IMAGINE THAT THERE ARE A LOT

804
00:58:53,890 --> 00:58:57,569
OF FUR SEALS.

805
00:58:57,590 --> 00:59:07,320
YES, BUT NOT WHAT
THEY USED TO BE.

806
00:59:07,340 --> 00:59:11,190
MY HUSBAND, PHIL ZAVADIL,
MOVED TO SAINT PAUL ISLAND

807
00:59:11,210 --> 00:59:15,130
IN 1998 TO WORK WITH THE
TRIBAL GOVERNMENT OF SAINT PAUL

808
00:59:15,150 --> 00:59:20,230
ON STARTING UP A NEW ECO
SYSTEM CONSERVATION OFFICE.

809
00:59:20,250 --> 00:59:23,630
- WHEN I FIRST GOT HERE,
THERE WAS PROBABLY 1.2 MILLION

810
00:59:23,650 --> 00:59:27,540
FUR SEALS ON THE PRIBS.

811
00:59:27,560 --> 00:59:31,110
HERE WE ARE, 10 YEARS LATER,
AND YOU KNOW, I THINK THEY'RE

812
00:59:31,130 --> 00:59:38,520
UNDER 600,000 FUR SEALS NOW.

813
00:59:38,540 --> 00:59:42,190
UNLESS WE DO SOMETHING
DIFFERENT, I DON'T SEE

814
00:59:42,210 --> 00:59:50,260
ANYTHING GETTING ANY BETTER.

815
00:59:50,280 --> 00:59:52,930
- THE UNITED STATES
GOVERNMENT REMAINS RESPONSIBLE

816
00:59:52,950 --> 00:59:55,700
FOR THE WELFARE OF THE FUR
SEALS UNDER THE MARINE MAMMAL

817
00:59:55,720 --> 01:00:00,000
PROTECTION ACT.

818
01:00:00,20 --> 01:00:02,610
THE TRIBAL GOVERNMENTS ARE
WORKING WITH THE NATIONAL

819
01:00:02,630 --> 01:00:05,880
MARINE FISHERY SERVICE TO
CO-MANAGE THE FUR SEAL HERD

820
01:00:05,900 --> 01:00:11,180
ON THE PRIBILOF ISLANDS.

821
01:00:11,200 --> 01:00:12,819
- THE NORTHERN FUR SEALS
ARE FACING A LOT OF THE SAME

822
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:17,350
THREATS THAT MARINE MAMMALS
THROUGHOUT THE BERING SEA FACE.

823
01:00:17,370 --> 01:00:20,460
THERE'S THE POTENTIAL
OF COMPETITION FOR PREY

824
01:00:20,480 --> 01:00:23,160
WITH COMMERCIAL FISHERIES.

825
01:00:23,180 --> 01:00:25,460
THE PRIMARY PREY FOR FUR
SEALS ON THE PRIBILOFS

826
01:00:25,480 --> 01:00:26,800
IS WALLEYE POLLOCK.

827
01:00:26,820 --> 01:00:32,940
IT'S ALSO THE LARGEST
FISHERY IN ALASKA.

828
01:00:32,960 --> 01:00:34,910
THERE'S PREDATION.

829
01:00:34,930 --> 01:00:36,609
KILLER WHALES TAKE
NORTHERN FUR SEALS ALL

830
01:00:36,630 --> 01:00:41,410
AROUND THE PRIBILOF ISLANDS.

831
01:00:41,430 --> 01:00:42,649
THERE'S DISEASE.

832
01:00:42,670 --> 01:00:45,520
DISEASE HAS ALWAYS BEEN
PRESENT IN ANIMAL POPULATIONS,

833
01:00:45,540 --> 01:00:47,80
BUT COULD INCREASE.

834
01:00:47,100 --> 01:00:49,620
IT COULD BE BROUGHT IN BY AN
OUTSIDE SOURCE, OR SOMETHING

835
01:00:49,640 --> 01:00:54,190
ELSE COULD TRIGGER
AN EPIDEMIC OF SORTS.

836
01:00:54,210 --> 01:00:55,760
THERE'S ALSO ENTANGLEMENTS.

837
01:00:55,780 --> 01:00:59,500
PACKING BANDS, TRAWL NET,
MONOFILAMENT.

838
01:00:59,520 --> 01:01:01,370
ALL THESE THINGS THAT CAN COME
OFF OF FISHING BOATS OR OTHER

839
01:01:01,390 --> 01:01:07,970
BOATS THAT FUR SEALS
CAN BECOME ENTANGLED IN.

840
01:01:07,990 --> 01:01:10,540
AND THEN THERE'S
CLIMATE CHANGE.

841
01:01:10,560 --> 01:01:14,140
AS WE SEE A WARMING OF
TEMPERATURES AND RECEDING

842
01:01:14,160 --> 01:01:18,819
OF THE ICE PACK IN THE BERING
SEA, IT COULD CERTAINLY AFFECT

843
01:01:18,840 --> 01:01:25,190
FUR SEAL BEHAVIOR, AS WELL AS
THE AVAILABILITY OF PREY.

844
01:01:25,210 --> 01:01:28,790
SO COLLECTIVELY, ALL OF THOSE
THREATS TOGETHER MOST LIKELY

845
01:01:28,810 --> 01:01:30,660
HAVE SOME SORT OF INFLUENCE.

846
01:01:30,680 --> 01:01:33,930
AND WE'RE JUST TRYING TO TEASE
OUT WHICH ONE, OR MAYBE SOME

847
01:01:33,950 --> 01:01:41,240
OTHER MIGHT BE
AFFECTING THE DECLINE.

848
01:01:41,260 --> 01:01:42,640
- WE NEED TO DO SOMETHING.

849
01:01:42,660 --> 01:01:48,609
THERE'S NOT GOING TO BE ONE
SIMPLE ANSWER, AND IT'S NOT

850
01:01:48,630 --> 01:01:50,650
GOING TO HAPPEN OVERNIGHT.

851
01:01:50,670 --> 01:01:52,880
I MEAN, IT'S TAKEN
US A COUPLE HUNDRED

852
01:01:52,900 --> 01:01:57,550
YEARS TO GET HERE, AND THAT'S
PROBABLY HOW LONG IT'S GOING

853
01:01:57,570 --> 01:02:03,630
TO TAKE TO GET THINGS
BACK ON TRACK.

854
01:02:03,650 --> 01:02:19,340
I FEEL HOPEFUL, AND EQUALLY,
I FEEL UNCERTAIN.

855
01:02:19,360 --> 01:02:26,580
[WOMAN SPEAKING UNANGAM
TUNUU LANGUAGE]

856
01:02:26,600 --> 01:02:28,490
- KLUUCHIN.
- KLUUCHIN.

857
01:02:28,510 --> 01:02:33,220
- HOPEFULNESS AND UNCERTAINTY
