865
01:02:54,230 --> 01:02:56,880
A WAY OF SOLVING PROBLEMS.

866
01:02:56,900 --> 01:02:58,80
IT'S A LOSS.

867
01:02:58,100 --> 01:03:03,650
IT'S A LOSS THAT
HURTS ALL OF US.

868
01:03:03,670 --> 01:03:07,290
THERE ARE FEWER THAN 200
PEOPLE LEFT WHO GREW UP

869
01:03:07,310 --> 01:03:10,529
SPEAKING UNANGAM TUNUU.

870
01:03:10,550 --> 01:03:16,630
MARY IS ONE OF THEM.

871
01:03:16,650 --> 01:03:35,990
HOPEFULLY, MY NEPHEW
WILL BECOME ANOTHER.

872
01:03:36,10 --> 01:03:39,690
- I WANT TO GET TRADITIONAL
TATTOOS LIKE MY MOM'S.

873
01:03:39,710 --> 01:03:43,260
THE LITTLE BLUE MOONS AND
THE DOT ON THE OTHER SIDE

874
01:03:43,280 --> 01:03:46,130
OF THE CRESCENT IS TO
REPRESENT THAT THE MOON

875
01:03:46,150 --> 01:03:51,270
IS ALWAYS WHOLE, EVEN WHEN
IT DOESN'T APPEAR TO BE.

876
01:03:51,290 --> 01:03:54,940
- ALONG WITH MY DAUGHTER,
KATIA, MY SISTER, STEPHANIE,

877
01:03:54,960 --> 01:03:58,110
AND OTHERS IN THE COMMUNITY,
WE'VE INITIATED A TRADITIONAL

878
01:03:58,130 --> 01:03:59,740
DANCE GROUP.

879
01:03:59,760 --> 01:04:03,210
- FOR OUR DANCE, WHENEVER
WE PERFORM--I WANT

880
01:04:03,230 --> 01:04:06,420
THIS ONE RIGHT HERE.

881
01:04:06,440 --> 01:04:07,950
-THE SEAL HEAD?
- MM-HMM.

882
01:04:07,970 --> 01:04:10,549
- IT WILL FACE THE--

883
01:04:10,570 --> 01:04:12,60
- FACE IN?

884
01:04:12,80 --> 01:04:14,560
- MM-HMM.
- THIS ONE?

885
01:04:14,580 --> 01:04:17,190
- YOURS DO THAT, TOO?

886
01:04:17,210 --> 01:04:20,560
- DO THEY?
- YEAH, THEY DO.

887
01:04:20,580 --> 01:04:22,69
- YOU THOUGHT THEY
WERE FRECKLES, HUH?

888
01:04:22,90 --> 01:04:24,70
[LAUGHTER]

889
01:04:24,90 --> 01:04:25,770
- YOU SAID IT WOULD GO THE
OPPOSITE WAY, THE OTHER

890
01:04:25,790 --> 01:04:26,800
WAY, RIGHT? ON THE OTHER CHEEK.

891
01:04:26,820 --> 01:04:28,910
- NO, THE SEALS--
OH, YEAH. THE OPPOSITE.

892
01:04:28,930 --> 01:04:34,40
IT'S LIKE A MIRROR IMAGE.

893
01:04:34,60 --> 01:04:37,509
I LIKE IT WHEN MY MOM
COMES TO ANCHORAGE.

894
01:04:37,530 --> 01:04:40,520
I LIKE TO WALK BEHIND HER
IN PUBLIC PLACES AND WATCH

895
01:04:40,540 --> 01:04:43,150
PEOPLE'S REACTIONS
AS WE'RE WALKING BY.

896
01:04:43,170 --> 01:04:44,220
- OH.

897
01:04:44,240 --> 01:04:46,560
- SHE GETS A LOT
OF DOUBLE TAKES?

898
01:04:46,580 --> 01:04:48,560
- MM-HMM.

899
01:04:48,580 --> 01:04:52,299
WHEN I FIRST DREW THEM, I WANTED
TO GET THEM PERMANENTLY DONE.

900
01:04:52,320 --> 01:04:55,000
I WANTED TO JUST DO IT.
JUST DELVE RIGHT INTO IT.

901
01:04:55,20 --> 01:04:58,870
- AND WHEN I DID MY FACE,
I WANTED TO DO IT 12 YEARS

902
01:04:58,890 --> 01:05:01,640
EARLIER THAN I ACTUALLY DID
IT, BUT MAYBE THE TIMING

903
01:05:01,660 --> 01:05:04,980
WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN RIGHT THEN,
ANYWAY, BECAUSE I STILL HAD

904
01:05:05,000 --> 01:05:07,380
SOME THINGS THAT I
NEEDED TO EXPERIENCE.

905
01:05:07,400 --> 01:05:09,450
AND SO, IT'S
ALL ABOUT TIMING.

906
01:05:09,470 --> 01:05:12,20
THAT'S WHY I SAID YOU WILL
KNOW--WHEN THE TIMING IS

907
01:05:12,40 --> 01:05:16,90
RIGHT, YOU'LL KNOW.

908
01:05:16,110 --> 01:05:17,650
- OF COURSE, EVERYONE'S
GOING TO BE CURIOUS.

909
01:05:17,670 --> 01:05:20,20
YOU KNOW, LIKE, I'VE
SEEN PEOPLE ASK YOU,

910
01:05:20,40 --> 01:05:23,60
"ARE THOSE PERMANENT?"
OR "ARE THOSE REAL?"

911
01:05:23,80 --> 01:05:26,60
AND THOSE ARE GOOD QUESTIONS,
BUT THE BETTER QUESTIONS ARE,

912
01:05:26,80 --> 01:05:28,670
"WHAT DOES IT REPRESENT?"
"WHAT MADE YOU DO IT?"

913
01:05:28,690 --> 01:05:31,800
"WHY DID YOU DO IT?"

914
01:05:31,820 --> 01:05:34,470
TIMES HAVE CHANGED.
TIMES ARE CHANGING.

915
01:05:34,490 --> 01:05:36,509
TIMES WILL ALWAYS BE CHANGING.

916
01:05:36,530 --> 01:05:41,380
AND THIS IS MY CHOICE THEN TO
REPRESENT WHO I AM AND WHERE I

917
01:05:41,400 --> 01:05:44,950
COME FROM, WHETHER OR
WHETHER NOT PEOPLE LIKE IT.

918
01:05:44,970 --> 01:05:48,589
- IF AND WHEN YOU DO,
IF SOMEONE SAYS TO YOU,

919
01:05:48,610 --> 01:05:51,150
"ARE THOSE PERMANENT?,"
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO SAY?

920
01:05:51,170 --> 01:05:52,320
- I DON'T KNOW.

921
01:05:52,340 --> 01:05:55,290
I LIKE YOUR RESPONSE--
"ONLY AS PERMANENT AS I AM."

922
01:05:55,310 --> 01:05:57,259
- YEAH.

923
01:05:57,280 --> 01:05:58,830
YOU DIDN'T LOOK AT THEM YET.

924
01:05:58,850 --> 01:06:05,470
- I WANT TO SEE.

925
01:06:05,490 --> 01:06:13,209
[DRUM BEATING/SINGING]

926
01:06:13,230 --> 01:06:17,350
- IF MY CULTURAL BASIS IS
BASED ON A RELATIONSHIP TO

927
01:06:17,370 --> 01:06:22,89
SEALS AND SEA LIONS AND BIRDS,
WHEN THOSE ANIMALS ARE GONE,

928
01:06:22,110 --> 01:06:23,250
WE'RE GONE.

929
01:06:23,270 --> 01:06:26,790
THE ALEUT CULTURE
WILL NOT EXIST.

930
01:06:26,810 --> 01:06:30,590
THE HOPEFUL THING IS THAT WE
ARE RAISING YOUNG GENERATION

931
01:06:30,610 --> 01:06:38,470
PEOPLE WHO ARE REALLY
WANTING TO HAVE THAT BACK.

932
01:06:38,490 --> 01:06:42,970
- HOW CAN WE REALLY
SUSTAIN THE ISLAND?

933
01:06:42,990 --> 01:06:46,140
BUT IT'S REALLY UP TO THE
PEOPLE OF THE ISLAND TO MAKE

934
01:06:46,160 --> 01:06:53,319
THAT DECISION FOR THEMSELVES.

935
01:06:53,340 --> 01:06:56,390
- WHAT I WANT TO TELL
THE YOUNGER PEOPLE...

936
01:06:56,410 --> 01:07:02,730
BE PROUD THAT YOU'RE AN ALEUT.

937
01:07:02,750 --> 01:07:07,460
SOME PEOPLE CALL THOSE
ISLANDS OUT THERE ROCKS.

938
01:07:07,480 --> 01:07:09,730
THEY'RE MORE THAN ROCKS.

939
01:07:09,750 --> 01:07:13,470
THEY'RE OUR HOME.

940
01:07:13,490 --> 01:07:25,620
[APPLAUSE]

941
01:07:25,640 --> 01:07:42,799
[DRUM QUIETLY
BEATS STEADY PULSE]

942
01:07:42,820 --> 01:07:47,270
- AS I WEAVE THIS ALEUT BASKET,

943
01:07:47,290 --> 01:07:50,770
I'M USING MODERN MATERIAL.

944
01:07:50,790 --> 01:07:54,210
IT'S ACTUALLY TELEPHONE WIRE.

945
01:07:54,230 --> 01:07:59,250
BUT I'M USING A TECHNIQUE
THAT IS MOST LIKELY THOUSANDS

946
01:07:59,270 --> 01:08:04,20
OF YEARS OLD.

947
01:08:04,40 --> 01:08:09,830
AND AS I LOOK BACK
AT OUR HISTORY,

948
01:08:09,850 --> 01:08:15,29
THAT'S WHAT IT'S ALL ABOUT.

949
01:08:15,50 --> 01:08:26,279
WEAVING TIMES AND
PLACES TOGETHER.

950
01:08:26,300 --> 01:08:31,480
I THINK ABOUT THE LAYER UPON
LAYER OF PEOPLE'S PASSAGES

951
01:08:31,500 --> 01:08:36,720
HERE ON THE ISLAND...

952
01:08:36,740 --> 01:08:44,359
THROUGH DIFFERENT ERAS
FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS.

953
01:08:44,380 --> 01:08:50,370
AND THE NEXT BASKET WE WEAVE...

954
01:08:50,390 --> 01:08:52,840
WELL, IT'S GOING TO HAVE A BIT

955
01:08:52,859 --> 01:09:05,880
OF EACH ONE OF
THOSE INTERACTIONS.

956
01:09:05,899 --> 01:09:13,319
I DON'T EVER COMPLETE A BASKET
WITHOUT HAVING FIRST STARTED

957
01:09:13,340 --> 01:09:19,430
ANOTHER ONE.

958
01:09:19,450 --> 01:09:24,970
ALL OF MY BASKETS ARE
REALLY ONE BASKET INTERLACED

959
01:09:24,990 --> 01:09:33,279
AND WOVEN TOGETHER.

960
01:09:33,300 --> 01:09:37,680
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT THE RESULT
IS GOING TO BE, BUT YOU JUST

961
01:09:37,700 --> 01:09:42,689
KEEP WEAVING.

962
01:09:42,710 --> 01:09:48,930
YOU JUST KEEP THINGS GOING
THROUGH TIME FOR COMING

963
01:09:48,950 --> 01:10:10,849
GENERATIONS THAT
